snippet: The woman who died at a cryotherapy center in Henderson while giving herself a cold-air treatment died from lack of oxygen, the Clark County coroner’s office said.
abstract: Clark County coroner’s office reveals lack of oxygen was behind death of Rejuvenice employee Chelsea Ake-Salvacion whose body was discovered in cold air treatment chamber at Rejuvenice cryotherapy center in Henderson, Nevada.
lead_paragraph: The woman who died at a cryotherapy center in Henderson while giving herself a cold-air treatment died from lack of oxygen, the Clark County coroner’s office said.

headline.main: Nevada: Lack of Oxygen Is Cited in Death in Cryotherapy Tank
